name: onAppReady

API that will be triggered when live chat app is ready, which is after JavaScript has been
downloaded and initialized.

properties.name: type
properties.description:
Type of button, possible options are:
+ monitor - monitor button
+ text - text button
+ static - static image button
+ float - float image button
+ mobile-image - mobile image button
+ mobile-text - mobile text button
+ adaptive - adaptive button

properties.description: Campaign id of button

properties.name: click
properties.description:
Simulate click behavior, the same as user click on this chat
button.

properties.name: onStatusChange
properties.description:
Register callback,
which will be notified when status of current campaign changed.

name: onButtonWillDisplay
description:
API that will be triggered before certain button is rendered, providing useful API to get/set

params.name: button

name: MessageTransformVisitor
description:
Message list is different from form fields, as the original list of messages is uncertain and can
grow larger and larger. It might be inconvenient, if only `MessagesTransform` is provided as API.
Here, `MessageTransformVisitor` allows to register specific transform for certain types.

properties.name: type
properties.description:
Any type of `Message`, for example:
+ 'system-message'
+ 'agent-text-message'
+ 'visitor-text-message'
+ 'waiting-queue'
+ etc.

properties.name: transform
properties.description: Message transform

properties.name: onChange
properties.description:
Register callback function to
transform message in list.

properties.name: minimize
properties.description: Minimize current chat window

properties.name: close
properties.description: Close current chat window

properties.name: endChat
properties.description: End current chat

properties.name: on
properties.description:
Register callback for specific events. Accepted events are:
+ minimize - Trigger when chat window is minimized
+ close - Trigger when chat window is closed
+ endchat - Trigger when chat is ended

In short, function can also provide a visitor object containing key-value pairs, where key is the type
string and value is the callback function for that specific type.

properties.name: render
properties.description:
Render customized element. If callback provies an HTMLElement, original component will not be
rendered; if provides null, use original component instead.

Function also accepts a visitor for multiple callback registration.

Possible render types are:
+ 'prechat.header'
+ 'prechat.content'
+ 'prechat.footer'
+ 'chat.header'
+ 'chat.content'
+ 'chat.input'
+ 'chat.footer'
+ 'postchat.header'
+ 'postchat.content'
+ 'postchat.footer'
+ 'offline.header'
+ 'offline.content'
+ 'offline.footer'
+ '*.header'
+ '*.content'
+ '*.footer'
